    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "those solutions like rent control and housing mandates seem like they'd just end up hurting the market more in the long run or making it harder for anyone to build anything new. isn't it true that the most effective way to lower costs is actually just more supply through less regulation, and that these extra \"inclusive\" rules often just block the very progress you're talking about?",
