      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that deregulation is the only way to lower costs is a common one, but it often ignores the fact that high-density zoning is a primary driver of housing affordability in the first place. Without the regulatory framework that allows for efficient land use, cities struggle to build enough housing to meet demand, which drives prices up regardless of how many units are built. Therefore, the most effective approach is not to remove all regulations, but to implement smart, targeted policies that encourage density while protecting vulnerable populations from displacement.",
